<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-49-0713 </DOCNO><TEXT>Various magnetic-separation processes including magnetic coagulation/sedimentation,magnetic filtration, magnetic ion exchange, and magnetite addition arereviewed. Their general theories and principles are described. Theirvarious applications in water and wastewater are introduced with specialemphasis on removals of oil scale and heavy metals.</TEXT></DOC>